cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.IT. 

This paper deals with deep latent Gaussian models and their diffusion limit, which are topics related to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The use of neural nets to implement the drift and diffusion coefficients of the stochastic differential equation (SDE) also suggests the sub-categories of neural networks (cs.NE) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the development of a variational inference framework involves information theory (cs.IT).
